comments.body:
@lsm5 Absolutely! I'll update the draft PR (#28331) to add a non-blocking CI build job on the native RISE runner instead of jumping straight to release artifacts. That's the right approach.

@Honny1 Good point about cross-compilation as the eventual build path. Go's cross-compile support for riscv64 is solid. The native runner CI job would validate correctness, while release artifacts could later use cross-compilation from the existing amd64 runner.

I'll rework the PR to add an `Alt Arch Riscv64` CI job. Will report back shortly.

@Luap99 Fair points, thanks for the detailed reasoning. I understand the CI maintenance concern.

Since podman already cross-compiles for several architectures in Cirrus CI, would a PR adding `GOOS=linux GOARCH=riscv64` to the existing cross-build matrix in `contrib/cirrus/runner.sh` be welcome? That would validate compilation without any new CI system or native runners.

If not, I'm happy to close the PR and issue. Debian trixie and Fedora riscv64 SIG both packaging podman is a good outcome already.
